{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0d01238-9f06-49f2-a3f3-10ec0cc65f19","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the VSTest switches move to platform-native flags passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` still works through the `dotnet test` bridge. Platform-specific flags go after `--`.\n\n**Required packages** (add to your test project):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a7ced636-fe00-4ad7-9bd8-175eb3c039bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a code change request.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` - Microsoft.Testing.Platform has its own code coverage integration via `--coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage or you use `--collect` still\n\n\n- Blame-related flags like `--blame-crash`, `--blame-hang`, and `--blame-hang-timeout` work differently with the new runner. When using `dotnet test` as a bridge to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, many VSTest switches need to be passed through with `--` or replaced with platform-specific equivalents, though the exact mapping depends on whether you're running through `dotnet test` or directly via the test executable. I'm reconsidering the filter syntax for Microsoft.Testing.Platform—the `--treenode-filter` uses tree node paths rather than the VSTest-style key=value format, so I should clarify that `--filter` works with `dotnet test` as a bridge option, while the platform-specific filters go after the `--` separator.\n\nNow I'm identifying the required NuGet packages for each reporting feature: the TRX report extension, code coverage extension, crash dump extension, and hang dump extension all need to be referenced in the project. The command structure passes the category filter through `dotnet test`, then uses `--` to separate the platform-specific options like report format, coverage output, and dump configurations.","outputTokens":1307},"id":"bd54afbc-0d0c-40b9-b383-4bfd6346d726","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:46:00.222Z","parentId":"77eabb9c-5673-4a10-84ae-581ad157c998"}
